<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-08T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-08T08:00:00-05:00" n="625" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d625">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/12907:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-08T16:00:00+03:00">July 8,
                                    1941—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received July 8—1:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1315. The evacuation of children from Moscow continues and the evacuation
                            of women with children has now begun. It would appear from the general
                            preparations being made that the Soviet authorities intend to defend the
                            city against attacks.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>